<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="23" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1452,1418,1984]" pageId="6" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,526,1670,1696]" pageId="6" pageNumber="23">Distribution and ecology:—</emphasis>
The species occurs in 
<collectingCountry box="[785,870,1670,1696]" name="Bolivia" pageId="6" pageNumber="23">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[884,988,1671,1697]" name="Paraguay" pageId="6" pageNumber="23">Paraguay</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1048,1119,1670,1696]" name="Brazil" pageId="6" pageNumber="23">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, where it is registered in the Northeast (AL, BA, CE, MA, PB, PE, PI, RN, SE), Central-West (MS, MG) and Southeast (MG, SP) (INCT-Virtual Herbarium of Flora and Fungi; Flora of 
<collectingCountry box="[610,678,1742,1768]" name="Brazil" pageId="6" pageNumber="23">Brazil</collectingCountry>
2020). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Steudel" authorityYear="1840" baseAuthorityName="Bongard" baseAuthorityYear="1836" box="[772,1003,1742,1768]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Bauhinia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="6" pageNumber="23" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cheilantha">
<emphasis box="[772,1003,1742,1768]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="23">Bauhinia cheilantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be found in the arboreal or shrub Caatinga domains, seasonal forest, refuge areas, anthropized environments, as well as in Cerrado areas (
<bibRefCitation author="Vaz, A. M. S. F. &amp; Tozzi, A. M. G. A." pageId="6" pageNumber="23" pagination="55 - 143" refId="ref19377" refString="Vaz, A. M. S. F. &amp; Tozzi, A. M. G. A. (2003) Bauhinia ser. Cansenia (Leguminosae: Caesalpinioideae no Brasil). Rodriguesia 54: 55 - 143. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / 2175 - 78602003548305" type="journal article" year="2003">Vaz &amp; Tozzi 2003</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1452,1418,1984]" box="[189,1090,1850,1877]" pageId="6" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,323,1850,1876]" pageId="6" pageNumber="23">Phenology:</emphasis>
Registered with flowers and fruits in May and flower in December.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="23" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1452,1418,1984]" pageId="6" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,493,1886,1912]" pageId="6" pageNumber="23">Taxonomic discussion:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Steudel" authorityYear="1840" baseAuthorityName="Bongard" baseAuthorityYear="1836" box="[492,726,1886,1912]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Bauhinia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="6" pageNumber="23" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cheilantha">
<emphasis box="[492,726,1886,1912]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="23">Bauhinia cheilantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized, mainly, by the arboreous habit, unifoliolate compound leaves, lobate, similar to a cow’s leg, actinodromous venation, inflorescence in terminal raceme, and legume fruit with ligneous valves. Commonly known “pata de vaca”.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
